{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "04", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "01", "M": "48", "S": "09"}}, "news": [{"title": "Over 1.28 lakh pending land survey cases in Maharashtra", "para": "Maharashtra faces a backlog of over 1.28 lakh land survey cases, with resolutions averaging 121 days. The state is set to appoint licensed surveyors by March 2026, establishing clear criteria for their selection and operation. Plans are also in motion to adopt a system similar to other states, where property is officially measured before land sale deeds are registered, ensuring accurate records and streamlining the process.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/maharashtra-faces-over-128-lakh-pending-land-survey-cases/132163718?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-30102/132163718.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Protected Aravali land cleared of illegal walls, buildings in Gurugram", "para": "Authorities in Gurugram have reclaimed nearly three acres of protected Aravali land in Behrampur village, demolishing 11 illegal structures. This significant anti-encroachment drive targeted under-construction buildings and boundary walls on land vital for groundwater recharge and wildlife corridors. The action follows years of efforts to protect this ecologically sensitive region from unauthorized development and fragmentation.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/massive-anti-encroachment-drive-clears-protected-aravali-land-in-gurugram/132163699?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-2671348/132163699.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Telangana HC seeks HYDRAA, HMDA stand on three-year delay in acting against lake encroachments", "para": "The Telangana High Court has demanded explanations from HYDRAA and HMDA regarding their inaction against encroachments around Errakunta lake. An advocate's petition highlighted repeated complaints over three years, alleging selective enforcement and failure to protect the water body despite its notification. The court seeks details on steps taken to safeguard the lake and prevent illegal constructions, with the next hearing scheduled for July 16.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/telangana-hc-demands-action-on-errakunta-lake-encroachments-amid-allegations-of-inaction/132163672?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-109691/132163672.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}